Usage: createSpecialMarkLayerShape [-help] [-cutOutBlockInsts <string>]
                                   [-extendOuterX <float>]
                                   [-extendOuterY <float>] [-extendX <float>]
                                   [-extendY <float>] -layer <string>

-help                          # Prints out the command usage
-cutOutBlockInsts <string>     # inst names needed be cut out. Without
                               # -cutOutBlockInsts: all blocks are cut out.
                               # -cutOutBlockInsts {}: all blocks are NOT cut
                               # since this pattern cannot match anything
                               # (string, optional)
-extendOuterX <float>          # expand the marker layer shape in X direction.
                               # (float, optional)
-extendOuterY <float>          # expand the marker layer shape in Y direction.
                               # (float, optional)
-extendX <float>               # expand the instnace boudary to cut marker
                               # layer shape in X direction. (float, optional)
-extendY <float>               # expand the instnace boudary to cut marker
                               # layer shape in Y direction. (float, optional)
-layer <string>                # the layer names which we will create the 
                               # marker layer shape on it. (string, required)